# HTTPS & OAuth Configuration

## Port Reference

| Service | HTTP Port | HTTPS Port | Notes |
|---------|-----------|------------|-------|
| Supabase API | 54321 | 54421 | Via HTTPS proxy |
| Supabase DB | 54322 | â€” | Direct connection |
| Supabase Studio | 54323 | â€” | Web UI |
| Next.js Dev | 3000 | 3000 | HTTPS via dev server |
| Background Worker | 8081 | 8080 | Via HTTPS proxy |
| Text Extractor | 8001 | 8000 | Via HTTPS proxy |

## Required Environment Variables

```bash
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://127.0.0.1:54421   # HTTPS proxy, never HTTP 54321
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=wss://localhost:3000             # wss://, never ws://
SLACK_REDIRECT_URI=https://localhost:3000/api/slack/oauth/callback
```

## Development Startup

```bash
yarn dev:https    # âś… Always use â€” starts all services with HTTPS
# Never use: yarn dev (HTTP-only, breaks OAuth)
```

## OAuth Flow

1. App calls `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth({ redirectTo: 'https://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback' })`
2. Supabase (`https://127.0.0.1:54421`) redirects to OAuth provider
3. Provider redirects back to `https://127.0.0.1:54421/auth/v1/callback`
4. Supabase exchanges code, redirects to Next.js API route
5. API route (`/api/auth/callback`) calls `exchangeCodeForSession(code)`, resolves redirect, sends user to final destination

## OAuth Configuration (3 places must match exactly)

1. **`supabase/config.toml`**: `redirect_uri = "https://127.0.0.1:54421/auth/v1/callback"` + `additional_redirect_urls` includes Next.js callbacks
2. **OAuth Provider Console** (Google/Slack/Microsoft): Authorized redirect URI = `https://127.0.0.1:54421/auth/v1/callback`
3. **`.env.local`**: All URLs use HTTPS

## Implementation Rules

- Build callback URLs from `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, never hardcode
- Exchange OAuth codes immediately (single-use, expire quickly)
- Handle both server-side code flow AND client-side hash fragment (PKCE) flow
- Use `window.location.search` for params in callback page (not `useSearchParams` â€” causes Suspense)
- HashFragmentHandlerInner in ClientLayout handles PKCE fallback
- Check route type before enforcing onboarding (admin/marketing routes bypass)

## SSL for Localhost

All services disable SSL verification for localhost (self-signed certs):
- Python: `httpx.Client(verify=False)` / `requests.post(verify=False)`
- Node.js: `NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0` via `lib/utils/tls.ts`

Only applies to `127.0.0.1`/`localhost` in development mode.

## Common Issues

| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| 404 on Supabase REST | Start HTTPS proxy: `yarn supabase:https-proxy` |
| WebSocket connection failed | Change `ws://` to `wss://` |
| `redirect_uri_mismatch` | All 3 config places must match exactly |
| Code exchange fails | Codes are single-use and expire fast â€” exchange immediately |
| HTTPS cert errors | Run `mkcert -install`, accept cert in browser |
